text:
With what delight I go to meet my doom;
The thought of wounds has filled my gaze with grace
And made a garden of that killing-place.

My life, Asad, hangs waiting for one glance;
The moth who burns shall advocate my case,
And argue with its death for your embrace.

Those wearied by the journey of the gaze
Now choose seclusion from the worldly race;
The wine-cup is a blister on their pace.

Each atom of a sigh, a peacock poised,
Prepared to show its beauty and its grace;
My God, my breath is dust from what bright place?

My collar, torn by love's beseeching art,
Reflects the prideful tilt of your cap's lace;
I am the mirror of that haughty grace.
